Help.#cdata:
Syntax: AXIS<1...99> <options>; 

Controls the location, values, and appearance of the axes in plots and charts. 

Used by: GBARLINE, GCHART, GCONTOUR, GRADAR, G3D procedures

Associates formats with variables.

Syntax:
(1) FORMAT variable-1 <... variable-n> <format> <DEFAULT=default-format>;

(2) FORMAT variable-1 <... variable-n> format <DEFAULT=default-format>;

(3) FORMAT variable-1 <... variable-n> format variable-1 <... variable-n> format;

If you omit DEFAULT=, SAS uses BESTw. as the default numeric format and $w. as the 
default character format.

Associates informats with variables.

Syntax:
(1) INFORMAT variable-1 <...variable-n> <informat>;  
(2) INFORMAT <variable-1> <... variable-n> <DEFAULT=default-informat>;  
(3) INFORMAT variable-1 <...variable-n> informat <DEFAULT=default-informat>;

Assigns descriptive labels to variables.

Syntax:
(1) LABEL variable-1='label-1' ... <variable-n='label-n'>; 

(2) LABEL variable-1=' ' ... <variable-n=' '>;

Syntax: WHERE where-expression-1 
  < logical-operator where-expression-n>; 

Selects observations from SAS data sets that meet a particular condition.

Associates a SAS fileref with an external file or an output device;
disassociates a fileref and external file; lists attributes of external files.

Syntax:

(1) FILENAME fileref <device-type> 'external-file' <ENCODING='encoding-value'>
    <options><operating-environment-options>;

(2) FILENAME fileref <device-type><options> <operating-environment-options>;

(3) FILENAME fileref CLEAR | _ALL_ CLEAR;

(4) FILENAME fileref LIST | _ALL_ LIST; 

(5) FILENAME fileref CATALOG 'catalog' <catalog-options>; 

(6) FILENAME fileref CLIPBRD <BUFFER=paste-buffer-name>; 

(7) FILENAME fileref EMAIL <'address' ><email-options>; 

(8) FILENAME fileref FTP 'external-file' <ftp-options>; 

(9) FILENAME fileref SFTP 'external-file' <sftp-options>; 

(10) FILENAME fileref SOCKET 'hostname:portno' <tcpip-options>;  

(11) FILENAME fileref SOCKET ':portno' SERVER <tcpip-options>;  

(12) FILENAME fileref URL 'external-file' <url-options>; 

(13) FILENAME filref WEBDAV 'external-file' <webdav-options>; 

(14) FILENAME fileref DDE 'DDE-triplet' <DDE-options>;

Associates or disassociates a SAS data library with a libref (a shortcut name); 
clears one or all librefs; lists the characteristics of a SAS data library; 
concatenates SAS data libraries; implicitly concatenates SAS catalogs.

Syntax:

(1) LIBNAME libref <engine> 'SAS-data-library' < options > <engine/host-options>;

(2) LIBNAME libref CLEAR | _ALL_ CLEAR;

(3) LIBNAME libref LIST | _ALL_ LIST;

(4) LIBNAME libref <engine> (library-specification-1 <... library-specification-n>) < options >; 

(5) LIBNAME libref INFOMAPS MAPPATH="location" <options>; 

(6) LIBNAME libref XML <'SAS-library | XML-document-path' > <basic-options> <NLS-options> <advanced-options>; 

(7) LIBNAME libref SASEDOC 'path' <sasedoc-engine-option> <options>;

(8) LIBNAME libref <engine-name> <physical-file-name> <SAS/ACCESS-engine-connection-options> 
      <SAS/ACCESS-libname-options>;

Begins a DATA step and provides names for any output SAS data sets, views, or programs. 

Syntax: 

(1) DATA <data-set-name-1 <(data-set-options-1)>> 
      <... data-set-name-n <(data-set-options-n)>> </ <DEBUG> <NESTING> <STACK = stack-size>> <NOLIST>;  

(2) DATA _NULL_ </ <DEBUG> <NESTING> <STACK = stack-size>> <NOLIST>;  

(3) DATA view-name <data-set-name-1 <(data-set-options-1)>> 
      <... data-set-name-n <(data-set-options-n)>> / 
      VIEW=view-name <(<password-option><SOURCE=source-option>)> <NESTING> <NOLIST>;  

(4) DATA data-set-name / PGM=program-name <(<password-option><SOURCE=source-option>)> <NESTING> <NOLIST>;  

(5) DATA VIEW=view-name <(password-option)> <NOLIST>;  
      DESCRIBE;  

(6) DATA PGM=program-name <(password-option)> <NOLIST>;  
      <DESCRIBE;>  
      <REDIRECT INPUT | OUTPUT old-name-1 = new-name-1<... old-name-n = new-name-n>;>  
      <EXECUTE;>
